#refine[
  Vegetation is a common part of procedurally generated environments. 
  Level of detail techniques are used to reduce resource consumption based on distance without affecting perceivable quality.
  This thesis aims to explore applicable tree generation algorithms that could support level of detail for creating vast worlds in real-time.
  To this end, we present an optimized version of Space Colonization written in Rust.
]
